  "description": "Rapid-growing annual from Amaranthaceae, native to Central and western Asia. Produces large, triangular or rounded leaves with powdery (farinose) surface; purple cultivars exhibit deep anthocyanin coloration. Heat- and drought-tolerant; grows 4–6 feet tall. Matures in 40–50 days; early bolting but short-season annual makes multiple plantings possible.",
  "name": "Atriplex hortensis",
